 Define the Parameters
    You need the following parameters:

        z_k (Vertical position of O1 atoms in the 4A layer)
        y_k (Y position of O1 atoms in the 4A layer)
        x_k (X position of O1 atoms in the 4A layer)

1. To calculate z_k (Vertical position of O1 atoms):

        (i)Go to the folder z_THE_O1.

        (ii)Run the driver.sh script, which calculates the density of O1 atoms in the 4A layer of theophylline (THE).

        (iii)Then, run the Python script get_surface_structure_CV_parameter_values.py from this folder. This will provide the value of z_k.

2. To calculate y_k (Y position of O1 atoms):

        (i)Go to the folder y_THE_O1.

        (ii)Run the driver.sh script, which calculates the density of O1 atoms in the 4A THE layer.

        (iii)Then, run the corresponding Python script from this folder to get the value of y_k.

3. To calculate x_k (X position of O1 atoms):

        (i) Navigate to the folder THE_O1_y_row_1.

        (ii) Inside, find the folder x_THE_O1 and run the driver.sh script from there.

        (iii)Once done, go one folder back and run the Python script from the THE_O1_y_row_1 folder to obtain x_k.
        
4. Repeat the process for the following folders:

THE_O1_y_row_2
THE_O1_y_row_3
THE_O1_y_row_4

5. Plug the values into the Plumed file:

(i)Now, go to the surf_struct_CV folder.
(ii)In this folder, you'll find a Plumed file. This file needs to be updated with the x_k, y_k, and z_k values you obtained from the steps above.

6. Post-process the trajectory:

After updating the Plumed file with the parameters, post-process the trajectory with this file to check the values of the surface structure CV.



